The Martial Arts Ontology (MAon)

Current version:
1.1
IRI:
http://EncodingActs.github.io/annotated/MAOcorpus
Author(s):
Yumeng HOU ORCID
Introduction:
The MAon Version 1.1 describes martial arts as an entity of embodied knowledge on top of intangible cultural heritage. Upgraded from its previous iteration, MAon Version 1.1 expands on the technical characteristics with philosophical considerations, consequently providing new perspectives for interpreting the embodied knowledge in martial arts.
The Named Individuals delivers a comprehensive semantic datafication of essential technical concepts in three iconic styles of Southern Chinese Martial Art (Hung Kuen, White Crane, and Choy Li Fut) and an instantiation of the entire Taming the Tiger Fist form set.
Visualisation :
WebVowl
